
<sellerabr>HEPWORTH</sellerabr> SELLS U.S. UNIT TO <purchabr>GLOBE MACHINE</purchabr>
    LONDON, April 13 - <seller>Hepworth Ceramic Holdings Plc</seller> {<sellercode>HEPC.L</sellercode>}
said it had agreed to sell its {<acquired>Western Plastics Corp</acquired>} unit to
{<purchaser>Globe Machine Manufacturing Co</purchaser>} for <dlramt>16.25 mln dlrs</dlramt> cash.
    <acqabr>Western</acqabr>, which makes <acqbus>polystyrene foam and container
products</acqbus>, has net assets of 19.3 mln dlrs and reported a 1986
pre-tax profit of 0.9 mln.
    The proceeds of the sale would be used to reduce borrowings
and develop activities in the U.K.
    <sellerabr>Hepworth</sellerabr> shares eased 0.5p on the announcement to 227.5p.
